.NET Framework 3.5.name: VRTK_Control
.NET Framework 3.5.summary: All 3D controls extend the VRTK_Control abstract class which provides a default set of methods and events that all of the subsequent controls expose.

methods.name: Awake()
GetContent()
methods.summary: The GetContent method returns the current game object of the control's content.
methods.returns: The currently stored content for the control.

methods.name: GetNormalizedValue()
methods.summary: The GetNormalizedValue method returns the current value mapped onto a range between 0 and 100.
methods.returns: The current normalized value of the control.

methods.name: GetThirdDirection(Vector3 axis1, Vector3 axis2)
methods.syntax: protected Vector3 GetThirdDirection(Vector3 axis1, Vector3 axis2)
methods.linkedSyntax: protected Vector3 GetThirdDirection(Vector3 axis1, Vector3 axis2)

methods.name: GetValue()
methods.summary: The GetValue method returns the current value/position/setting of the control depending on the control that is extending this abstract class.

methods.name: SetContent(GameObject content, bool hideContent)
methods.summary: The SetContent method sets the given game object as the content of the control. This will then disable and optionally hide the content when a control is obscuring its view to prevent interacting with content within a control.

params.value: The content to be considered within the control.
When true the content will be hidden in addition to being non-interactable in case the control is fully closed.

methods.syntax: public virtual void SetContent(GameObject content, bool hideContent)
methods.linkedSyntax: public virtual void SetContent(GameObject content, bool hideContent)

Update()

events.summary: Emitted when the 3D Control value has changed.
